    "description":  "English\n\nThe Way of Immortals prevails across the mainland of the Nine States, and everyone pursues to enter an Immortal Sect. However, the peace is disrupted when a crack suddenly appears in the boundary wall, allowing a tribe of alien demons to infiltrate the Immortal Sect to seize power and rule over the mainland of the Nine States. Mu Xun, a sword immortal, embarks on a battle to stop the invasion of the demon tribe along with his friends. Unfortunately, Mu Xun falls into a trap set by the demons and is wrongly accused of betraying the Immortal Sect. In order to uncover clues to the presence of the lurking demons, Mu Xun decides to hide his true identity and sends his only son, Dongfang Hao, to be raised by his wife\u0027s clan. Although Dongfang Hao bears the blood of the imperial clan, he is perceived as an ordinary person and is often bullied by his peers due to his untapped potential. He was originally the son of the Sword Immortal, but his fate was bumpy due to his father being framed by the demons. However, in critical moments, Dongfang Hao can always save the day through his relentless efforts, gradually attaining immortality. Whether in the Secret Realm of Taichu or the imperial city of Emperor Zhaowu, Dongfang Hao fearlessly comes to the aid of his friends in distress. Meanwhile, he never forgets his mission to search for his missing father. Through training the flood dragon and capturing the immortal spirit, Dongfang Hao keeps improving his cultivation to rescue his father and rally all Immortal Schools to drive the demon tribe away from the mainland of the Nine States.",
